British taekondo fighter Aaron Cook has confirmed he plans to compete for Moldova at the 2016 Olympics in Rio .
Dorset-born Cook , who was overlooked for the Great Britain taekwondo squad at London 2012 applied for citizenship after receiving funding from Moldovan billionaire Igor Iuzefovici and has received his passport from the eastern European state .
Cook has refused to compete under the British flag since May 2012 .